race.comment: COMMANDS SUCCESS (1) finds the right race third up. His return at Seymour was good in a solidly run race before being pitched up in grade at Flemington and battling on fairly for a midfield finish. He comes back a couple of grades now and should prove hard to hold out. MR ASSERTIVE (2) was okay in a BM66 at Flemington when last seen but had been knocking on the door in this grade prior. He's got early speed and draws to use it. BOHEMIAN ANGEL (8) resumes with a handy profile, having won her maiden as an odds-on favourite when fresh last time in. She should be hard to hold out. BRAVE CAROL (9) was good fresh at Terang and has claims with fitness improvement to come.
